Consistent naming conventions improve resource management and operational efficiency.

A good naming convention typically includes:

* Organization
* Environment
* Region
* Resource type
* Sequence number

Example:
prod-eastus-webvm-01

Benefits include:

* Easier identification
* Better automation
* Simplified troubleshooting
* Consistent governance

A real-life use case is multinational organizations managing thousands of Azure resources across multiple subscriptions.

Standardized naming conventions reduce administrative errors and improve operational visibility.
